race.comment: CELEBRITY ANGEL (10) peaks off narrow defeats here 2x and at Geraldton the latest. She has the early speed to clear the awkward barrier and Pike replaces the 3kg apprentice. She's been heavily bet and this is a winnable race with average luck in the run. BUBBLES IN RIO (2) resumed from a spell beaten 2L at Bunbury. She's raced well in stronger including at Stakes level. Has placed 2/3 second up and is a strong chance to break through. HELLAVAMOMENT (6) won two trials and was beaten 1.3L on debut, beating home the above. Should improve sharply off that and can make the finish with average luck from a sticky gate. SALTY MISS (3) has the outside barrier to contend with, but she was narrowly beaten here first-up and has more to give.
